    b"    Choose memory search hints for the selected task and current request.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a   "
    b"     The hints will drive memory search before the selected task runs.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a      "
    b"  Stop once the hints look good enough for the request without thinking about it"
    b" too much.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Search surfaces:\x0d\x0a        - tags: exact memory tags. They "
    b"are not substring searched.\x0d\x0a        - strings.contains: case-insensitive text f"
    b"ragments. Each value is checked\x0d\x0a          as a substring against searchable mem"
    b"ory content.\x0d\x0a        - strings.equals: exact text values. Each value is checked"
    b" for exact\x0d\x0a          equality against searchable memory content.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Opt"
    b"ional outputs available in this step:\x0d\x0a        - candidate_memory: a vague remem"
    b"bered observation that could be useful to\x0d\x0a          preserve.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Rules:"
    b"\x0d\x0a        - Return only search hints and optional candidate_memory.\x0d\x0a        - S"
    b"earch hints are alternatives during retrieval; a memory can be useful\x0d\x0a         "
    b" when any positive tag or string hint matches.\x0d\x0a        - Prefer tags.any_of for"
    b" positive tag hints.\x0d\x0a        - Leave tags.all_of empty unless compatibility wit"
    b"h older memories needs it.\x0d\x0a        - Use tags.none_of only for clear exclusions"
    b".\x0d\x0a        - Use strings.contains for durable words or phrases that should appea"
    b"r\x0d\x0a          inside a relevant memory.\x0d\x0a        - Use strings.equals only for ex"
    b"act text that should match a relevant\x0d\x0a          memory value as a whole.\x0d\x0a     "
